values.-1: I would prefer this is not merged as is

messages.message: Uploaded patch set 1.
Uploaded patch set 2: Patch Set 1 was rebased.

Patch Set 2:

I tested enabling scissor optimization on SGX540 now, on two Galaxy Nexus devices running Nougat, side by side. My conclusion is that while disabling it definitely helped on DDK 1.9, using OpenGL ES 1.1 renderer, it doesn't seem to have any positive impact on DDK 1.14, using OpenGL es 2.0 renderer. I'd go as far as saying that it's very marginally better if scissor optimization is enabled even, but it's hard to say that for sure.

tl;dr - if you see the same behavior on SGX544, let's remove this prop altogether.

Patch Set 2:

> tl;dr - if you see the same behavior on SGX544, let's remove this
 > prop altogether.

Yeah, and I can always bring this back in my device tree if need be. I'll probably make this a revert of the original commit.
